TextBody: ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000CLEIn:ref Oh hey Nicholas, we have another case going with a scheduling question and so I thought this was that. I can get it scheduled Thanks Jim Internal Use From: Netwrix Support Sent: Monday, December 2, 2024 10:53 AM To: Jim Callison Subject: [EXTERNAL] RE: 00413159 - SQL job stopped running and won't start [External Content] Please use caution. Hello Jim, I’m following up on my previous email with the scheduling availability link, as I haven’t seen a meeting scheduled yet. If you need me to resend the link or if you have any questions, please feel free to reply to this email. Looking forward to connecting with you! Ticket Number: 00413159 Ticket Subject: SQL job stopped running and won't start Ticket Details: We have an important production custom job that pulls login activity every few minutes across the environment. It has stopped running and will not start. We have traced and it seems to be missing a hostlist record. We have reviewed the host list adn it look good and all other jobs are running via the same host list. here is the call SELECT HM.Name,HM.FQDN,HM.hostID FROM SA_HostMasterTbl AS HM WHERE HM.hostID in (Select HostListsContentTbl.hostID from HostListsContentTbl where HostListsContentTbl.listID='{5D376271-0FAC-4B6B-A43A-9B26AAC0DC9D}') Thank you! Nicholas Zimmer ____________________ _________ Cybersecurity That Works for You 6160 Warren Parkway, Suite 100, Frisco, TX 75034 www.netwrix.com ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0CLEIn:ref
